        <h2 id="verdict">Is LongShot worth it in 2026? Final verdict</h2>
        <p><strong>For solo bloggers with writing skill: yes.</strong> $19/mo for a fact-checked first draft beats every comparable tool. FactGPT saves hours per article on sourcing, and Power Mode keeps drafts grounded in your real research.</p>

        <p><strong>For small content teams with an editor: yes, with a pairing.</strong> Add Surfer or Clearscope for SERP scoring and you have a tight $138–$168/mo stack. Still cheaper than Jasper + Surfer.</p>

        <p><strong>For business owners without writers: almost always no.</strong> LongShot gives you drafts. Drafts are not articles. You will spend $2,400+ per month in editor + publishing time to turn 30 LongShot drafts into ranked pages. At that math, a done-for-you platform costs less and ships faster.</p>

